    "The questionnaire used different response options for the questions, including yes/no and scales of 1-3 or 1-5.",
    "This differentiation aimed to better match the nature of each question, and may increase respondent engagement while reducing yea-saying bias (59).",
    "However, it inhibits direct comparison of items based on their mean score.",
    "Table 1 shows mean scores for the 38 items, with a 'normalized mean' column ranging from 0 to 1, which allows a clearer view of the drivers' agreement with statements across items.",
    "The results are interpreted below on this 0 to 1 scale."
